            <title>[CAMEL-7896] camel-netty-http producer should close the channel when the connection header is not keep alive</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-7896</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the http request connection header is &quot;keep alive&quot;, camel http producer will not close the channel. It can cause some trouble if the response connection header is &quot;close&quot;.  We need to close the channel if the response connection header is &quot;close&quot;. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
